choices.text: Before Cam broke his right arm, he was able to type an average of 9 words per minute on his phone for a total of 450 words (3 x 15) in five minutes. After he broke his arm, he had to use his left hand and could only type an average of 6 words per minute for a total of 300 words (2 x 15) in five minutes. Therefore, the difference between the number of words Cam was able to type before and after breaking his right arm is 450 - 300 = 150 words.
